#: ../../contacts/toc.rst:7
msgid "Working with Contacts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:5
msgid "In the Contacts component you can keep track of all the people with whom you exchange e-mails and group them in address books. Existing address books appear on the column on the right of the component's list.  You can create new contact by using the |new| button and selecting `New Contact`; they will be stored under the `Contacts` section of the Contacts component. You can also choose under which address book the new contact is stored. Additionally, mail-tags can be added to any contacts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:14
msgid "Addresses of people to whom you send an e-mail are automatically added to the `Emailed Contacts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:17
msgid "Deleted contacts land in the special `Trash` address book, which keeps them until you manually empty it. To do so, right-click the address book and select `Empty trash`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:21
msgid "A right-click on the address book allows to carry out a few action on it and its content: edit, share, empty, or delete it. Moreover, new address books can be created. For each contact, icons allow to carry out different actions: delete, move, or write an e-mail to the contact."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:27
msgid "To move the contacts from one address book to another, you can also drag the contact and drop it on the destination address book."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:31
msgid "If any colleague has shared an address book, you can click the :bdg-primary-line:`FIND SHARES` button under `Shared Address Book` and provide the e-mail address. You will see all the address books shared by the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:36
msgid "You can search among contacts using the search bar. You can then refine your search by clicking the :bdg-primary:`ADVANCED FILTER` button. Here you can also choose to include shared address books in the search."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:42
msgid "Configure a CardDav Client"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:44
msgid "Adding a |product| address book to your favourite CardDAV client is straightforward and requires only a few steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:47
msgid "In this scenario, the user *john.smith@example.com* wants to import in Mozilla's Thunderbird an address book from on the domain *mail.example.com*. In the remainder, replace these values with suitable ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:52
msgid "Step 1. New Address book"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:54
msgid "On your client, go to the Calendar and select **New Address Book**, providing the **Username** and the **Location**, which has format ``https://<domain>/dav/username``, so *https://mail.example.com/dav/john.smith@example.com*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:63
msgid "Step 2. Insert credentials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:65
msgid "Authenticate co |product| by inserting the username and password to access the address book."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:72
msgid "Step 3. Select Address Books"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:74
msgid "You will be then presented a list, from which to choose the address books to import in the client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:81
msgid "Other clients"
msgstr ""

#: ../../common/carbonio/usage/contacts.rst:83
msgid "You are now done! The imported address books will show up in the list of your client."
msgstr ""
